title: The Letters of a Post-Impressionist
creator: Vincent Van Gogh
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: “Being the Familiar Correspondence of Vincent Van Gogh ... [Van Gogh's] art was appreciated during his life only by a very few and it is but within recent years that it has found admirers who in many cases have been most ardently enthusiastic. Of the following letters, some were addressed to his brother and the remainder to his friend E. Bernard. (Summary from Preface) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the Librivox catalog page for this project For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org . Download M4B (182MB)
